<head>BREAST</head><list type="translations"><item xml:lang="zh">乳房</item></list>
<div type="definition">
<p>PAIR of BODY PARTS on the CHEST of WOMEN.</p></div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard term for the breast is apparently rǔ 乳, but since the breast of the woman was exceedingly rarely referred to in the non-excavated literature, it is hard to be sure whether the word was not something of a taboo in dignified discourse. Only Zhuangzi breaks the taboo. See NIPPLE.</p></div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>乳房</p>
<p>乳</p>
<p>奶</p>
<p>奶子</p>
